<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,323,1511,1537]" box="[151,323,1511,1537]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,323,1511,1537]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" reason="1">
<taxonomicName box="[151,323,1511,1537]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pantecphylini">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,323,1511,1537]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Pantecphylini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1586,1772]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
This monotypic tribe contains 
<number box="[507,536,1586,1612]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="17.0">17</number>
species, distributed widely in Central and West Africa. Members of this tribe are characterized by a strongly armed, spiny pronotum, and the presence of a unique abdomino-alary stridulatory mechanism, presumably used for defense. Recently a number of new species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1278,1436,1667,1692]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Pantecphylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1278,1436,1667,1692]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Pantecphylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been described from Central Africa (
<bibRefCitation author="Schmidt" box="[652,822,1706,1732]" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" refString="Schmidt, G. H. (2003) In Cameroon, two species of Pantecphylus Karsch, 1891 (Insecta: Orthopteroidea: Ensifera: Pseudophyllidae) are distributed. Bollettino di Zoologia Agraria e di Bachicoltura, 35 (3), 209 - 224. (*)" type="journal article" year="2003">Schmidt 2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schmidt" box="[835,910,1706,1732]" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" refString="Schmidt, G. H. (2006 a) A new species of Pantecphylus collected in Low Zaire (Democratic Republic Congo) (Orthoptera, Pseudophyllidae). Fragmenta entomologica, Roma, 38 (1), 1 - 6." type="journal article" year="2006" yearSuffix="a">2006a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schmidt" box="[923,1000,1706,1732]" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" refString="Schmidt, G. H. (2006 b) Description of six new species of Pantecphylus Karsch found in Central Africa near to, and in the north of the Equator (Democratic Republic Congo and South of Sudan) (Orthopteroidea, Ensifera, Tettigonoidea, Pseudophyllidae). Bollettino di Zoologia Agraria e di Bachicoltura, 38 (1), 1 - 25." type="journal article" year="2006" yearSuffix="b">
<number box="[923,985,1706,1732]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="2006.0">2006</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schmidt" box="[1013,1075,1706,1732]" pageId="4" pageNumber="26" refString="Schmidt, G. H. (2007) Two new Pantecphylus males from Kassai province (Democratic Republic Congo), and the problem of selecting conspecific females (Insecta, Orthopteroidea, Ensifera, Tettigonioidea, Pseudophyllidae). Bollettino di Zoologia Agraria e di Bachicoltura, 39 (1), 35 - 43." type="journal article" year="2007">
<number box="[1013,1075,1706,1732]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Schmidt et al. 
<number box="[1250,1315,1706,1732]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="2004.0">2004</number>
), but only two species have been recorded from the 
<collectionCode box="[636,723,1746,1772]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">GFWA</collectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
